Feather LoRa APRS Tracker — A LoRa APRS position tracker built on the Adafruit Feather M0 RFM96 (433MHz) for high-power rocket telemetry. Transmits real-time GPS position and flight data as standard TNC2 APRS packets over LoRa, compatible with the CA2RXU LoRa_APRS_Tracker/iGate network.
The tracker reads GPS coordinates from an Adafruit GPS FeatherWing on Serial1 and receives altitude/flight-state data from a companion altimeter board over a SERCOM1 UART link. It builds uncompressed APRS position packets with telemetry in the comment field and transmits them via LoRa at configurable intervals.
Radio settings match the CA2RXU LoRa APRS ecosystem: 433.775 MHz, SF12, 125 kHz bandwidth, coding rate 4/5, sync word 0x12. Any ground station or iGate running CA2RXU firmware will receive and decode the packets.
Built with PlatformIO and Arduino framework. Uses RadioLib for LoRa radio control and TinyGPSPlus for NMEA parsing.


This Code was based off on the work of :
https://github.com/richonguzman/LoRa_APRS_Tracker : CA2RXU LoRa APRS Tracker/Station

I wanted a tracker that would run on an Adafeather LoRa M0 and work with his ground station code so me and Claude made this. 
Please change the callsign and maybe the freq (currently 443.775) before use.
